%S A395011 2,5,16,91,182,1752,468,3507,946,6201,1664,28980,2670
%N A395011 Minimum lexicographic rank distance between Prüfer codes of a graceful labeling of a tree and its involution labeling.
%C A395011 Let T be a gracefully labeled tree on n vertices, and let T' be the labeling obtained from T by replacing each label v with n-1-v. Let P(T) and P(T') be the corresponding Prüfer codes. Then a(n) is the minimum value of |rank(P(T)) - rank(P(T'))|, where rank is taken in the lexicographically ordered set of all Prüfer codes of length n-2 over {0,1,...,n-1}, numbered from 1 to n^(n-2).
%D A395011 Douglas B. West, Introduction to Graph Theory, Pearson Education Pte. Ltd, 2002, page 81.
%H A395011 Igor Blokhin, <a href="https://github.com/IgorBlokhin/Graph-Theory">Graph Theory</a> (Python repository)
%e A395011 For n = 4, among two involution pairs of graceful labelings, the minimum distance is achieved for the Prufer codes (2, 0) and (3, 1). Their ranks among all 16 Prufer codes are 9 and 14, respectively, so the distance is 5. These codes correspond to graceful labelings of the path 1--2--0--3 and 0--3--1--2.
%Y A395011 Cf. A337274.
